sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id)
FROM goals
WHERE status = 'in progress';

SELECT DISTINCT user_id
FROM activity_data
WHERE activity_date < '2022-01-01' OR activity_date > '2022-01-31';

SELECT SUM(steps) AS total_steps
FROM activity_data
WHERE user_id = 5;

SELECT progress_value
FROM progress
WHERE goal_id = 0;

SELECT icon_url
FROM activity_types
WHERE activity_type_name = 'running';

SELECT ad.activity_type_id, COUNT(DISTINCT ad.user_id) AS num_users
FROM activity_data ad
GROUP BY ad.activity_type_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'sailors' refers to the users;
- 'ships' refers to the devices used by the users;
- 'realm of the briskly active' refers to the users who have an average step count greater than 5000, considered active in this context.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM user_roles 
WHERE role_id = (SELECT role_id FROM roles WHERE role_name = 'admin');

external_knowledge:
- "lighthouse guiding the fleet of steps" is a metaphor used here to refer to the user who has taken the most steps. This metaphorical expression suggests leadership in the context of step activity; 
- "fleet of steps" is a metaphorical way to describe the collective step counts of all users; 
- "leading the way" indicates the user has taken the highest number of steps among all users.
